strategy: 1. Create a consolidated "non_returned_sales" CTE that unions distinct (item_sk, customer_sk, d_date_sk, channel) from all three sales tables where no return exists, joining only with date_dim filtere
what_failed: Regression (0.39x): Consolidated the three independent anti-join aggregations into a single pass using UNION ALL, then computed all channel aggregates in one CTE with conditional aggregation. Added a filtered_date CTE to push the year 2000 filter early and avoid redundant date_dim scans.
why_it_failed: Created both filtered (store_sales_agg, web_sales_agg) AND original (ss, ws) versions of the same aggregations. The query does a 6-way self-join matching quarterly patterns (Q1->Q2->Q3). Duplicate CTEs doubled materialization and confused the optimizer's cardinality estimates for the multi-self-join.
